Last fall I had the unique opportunity to head to East Canton, Ohio to photograph the Titleist Pro V1 validation at Clearview Golf Club - the first golf course in the US to be built, owned, and operated by an African American. Former LPGA golfer Renee Powell graciously showed me around the course her family built in the 1940s. 📸 for Titleist

“Boston’s best bagel was real - then it vanished. How did it start? Where did it go? Who in the world was “Mike the Baker?” I had a blast working on this story for @bostonglobemag with Mike Geldart - the man behind Boston’s best bagel. Check out this fun story by Aaron Pressman #🥯

Brad Snyder (@bradsnyderusa) is a NAVY veteran, Team USA Paralympian, and now Rooney’s dad. I had the pleasure of meeting and photographing Brad and his family at their home this past summer for Team USA. Big thanks to the talented team at @freshtapemedia for bringing me onboard for this compelling project.

New work for Hasbro! Bolt was commissioned by the creative team at NERF to produce visual assets for the launch of the NERF Pro Stryfe X - the brand’s first high performance half dart blaster. Our team created several launch videos for digital use, as well as still images for social graphics, point-of-sale advertising, and in-arena branding for the debut of the accompanying new sport launch, Nerfball. Huge thanks to the talented creative team at NERF for bringing us onboard, and our incredible crew for making it happen!
